Introduction-

In this scenario, you are a project lead in an IT company. You and your team are working on a huge project, which consists of multiple functionalities and 
modules. This project is evolving over time and so your team is expecting a lot of code revisions.You'll configure your Git user information, create a local
Git repository, add a file to the repository, and do some basic operations like adding a file, editing files, and making commits.

********************
Installing Git-

sudo apt update
sudo apt install git
git --version

********************
Initializing a new repository-

mkdir my-git-repo
cd my-git-repo
git init

********************
Configuring Git-

git config --global user.name "Prateek"
git config --global user.email "iamprateek999@.com"

********************
Operations-

touch New_file
vim New_file
Inserting-: This is my first repository. Saving the file.
git status
git add New_file
git commit
Adding commit message-: This is my first commit!

********************
Re-editing-

vim New_file
Inserting-: A repository is a location where all the files of a particular project are stored. Saving the file.
git status
git diff New_file
git add New_file
git status
git commit -m "This is my second commit."
git log
